----------------------------
revision 1.965.2.10
date: 2005/10/21 03:17:41;  author: pfaedit;  state: Exp;  lines: +3 -3
Daniel Gillmor points out there is no way to set the Weight field of the OS/2 table in a script. And provides a patch to make this possible. It made me realize there is no way to set any of the OS/2 fields (except panose) and extend his patch.

patch with the following new scripting functions:
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â SetOS2Value("item-name", value)
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â GetOS2Value("item-name")
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â SetPrivateValue("item-key","item-value")
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â GetPrivateValue("item-key")
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â HasPrivateValue("item-key")
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â RemovePrivateValue("item-key")

SetPrivateValue
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Changes (or Adds) an entry to the font's private dictionary with
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  the given key and given value. Both must be strings. The key may
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  be anything, it is not limited to any set of expected keys.
GetPrivateValue
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Returns the string in the private dictionary which matches the
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  given key. If the key isn't in the dictionary it explodes.
HasPrivateValue
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Returns whether a key is in the dictionary
RemovePrivateValue
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Removes a key (and associated value) from the dictionary.
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Returns whether the key was in the dictionary (this is not a
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  typo).
SetOS2Value
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  The first argument must be one of the following strings. The
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  second argument is usually an integer, but VendorId takes a (4
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  character) string, and panose takes a 10 element integer array.
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Weight, Width, FSType, IBMFamily, VendorID, Panose,
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  WinAscent, WinAscentIsOffset
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  These are equivalent to the WinAscent field & []Offset
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  check box in Font Info->OS/2->Misc. Where
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  WinAscentOffset controls whether WinAscent is treated as
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  an absolute number or as relative to the expected
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  number.
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  WinDescent, WinDescentIsOffset,
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  TypoAscent, TypoAscentIsOffset,
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  TypoDescent, TypoDescentIsOffset,
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  HHeadAscent, HHeadAscentIsOffset,
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  HHeadDescent, HHeadDescentIsOffset,
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  TypoLineGap, HHeadLineGap, VHeadLineGap,
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  SubXSize, SubYSize, SubXOffset, SubYOffset,
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Sets the Subscript x/y sizes/offsets
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  SupXSize, SupYSize, SupXOffset, SupYOffset,
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Sets the Superscript x/y sizes/offsets
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  StrikeOutSize, StrikeOutPos
GetOS2Value
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  The argument takes the same set of tag strings. VendorId returns
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  a string, and Panose returns an array. The others return
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  integers.
----------------------------
revision 1.965.2.9
date: 2005/10/18 21:44:40;  author: pfaedit;  state: Exp;  lines: +2 -2
Oops. Ofm files where a glyph had more than 128 kerns didn't work.
----------------------------
revision 1.965.2.8
date: 2005/10/18 14:55:08;  author: pfaedit;  state: Exp;  lines: +3 -3
When outputting a mark-to-base feature with multiple mark classes, each base glyph may be used by several marks. We were adding the base glyph multiple times to the coverage table. Bad.
----------------------------
revision 1.965.2.7
date: 2005/10/18 04:44:59;  author: pfaedit;  state: Exp;  lines: +2 -2
KANOU points out that I was using rules too strict in parsing an svg poly command.
----------------------------
revision 1.965.2.6
date: 2005/10/17 23:36:37;  author: pfaedit;  state: Exp;  lines: +3 -3
Oh. It looks as though ofm files don't actually use the font direction field. Al
l files I've looked at have this set to 0 (Top to bottom, Left to Right) even the arabic only ones.
----------------------------
revision 1.965.2.5
date: 2005/10/17 02:01:45;  author: pfaedit;  state: Exp;  lines: +2 -2
I think I know enough to set font-direction for left-to-right vs right-to-left.
----------------------------
revision 1.965.2.4
date: 2005/10/16 18:25:05;  author: pfaedit;  state: Exp;  lines: +2 -2
